  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "UIAccessibilityAction",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " informal protocol provides a way for accessibility elements to support specific actions, such as selecting values in a range or scrolling through information on the screen. For example, to respond to a scrolling gesture, you implement the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/objectivec/nsobject/1615161-accessibilityscroll",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " method and post ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.uikit/documentation/UIKit/UIAccessibility/Notification/pageScrolled",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " with the new page status (such as “Page 3 of 9”). Or, to make an element such as a slider or picker view accessible, you first need to characterize it by including the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.uikit/documentation/UIKit/UIAccessibilityTraits/adjustable",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " trait. Then, you must implement the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/objectivec/nsobject/1615076-accessibilityincrement",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/objectivec/nsobject/1615169-accessibilitydecrement",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " methods. When you do this, assistive technology users can adjust the element using gestures specific to the assistive technology.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
